                <div class="job-des-dt142 policy-des-dt">
                    <h4>
                        Pricing and Payment
                    </h4>

                    <p>
                        Clearly display the prices of products, including any
                        applicable taxes, fees, and shipping costs. Ensure that the checkout process is secure and
                        offers various payment options, such as credit/debit cards, digital wallets, or bank transfers.
                    </p>

                </div>
                <div class="job-des-dt142 policy-des-dt">
                    <h4>
                        Shipping and Delivery
                    </h4>

                    <p>
                        Specify the shipping methods, estimated delivery times,
                        and any additional charges or restrictions related to shipping to specific locations. Address
                        issues like lost packages, damaged goods during transit, and provide a clear process for filing
                        complaints or seeking refunds.
                    </p>
                   
                </div>

                <div class="job-des-dt142 policy-des-dt">
                    <h4>
                        Returns and Refunds
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        Establish a fair and transparent return policy that allows
                        customers to return products within a reasonable timeframe. Clearly state the conditions for
                        returns, including whether the product must be unused, in its original packaging, and any
                        associated restocking fees. Outline the process for requesting refunds and the timeline for
                        processing them.

                    </p>
                    
                </div>
                <div class="job-des-dt142 policy-des-dt">
                    <h4>
                        Customer Support
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        Provide accessible and responsive customer support channels,
                        such as email, live chat, or phone. Clearly communicate the expected response times and
                        support hours. Train customer support staff to handle inquiries, complaints, and resolve issues
                        efficiently and professionally.
                    </p>
                   

                </div>

